{"title_page": "Hanuman Junction", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2018}}\n{{For|the same-titled 2001 Telugu film by [[M. Raja]]|Hanuman Junction (film)}}{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Hanuman Junction\n| demographics_type1              = [[Languages]]\n| government_type                 = [[Panchayiti]]\n| governing_body                  = Bapulapadu Panchayiti\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = <ref name=civicbody />\n| area_rank                       = \n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| population_demonym              = \n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| named_for                       = \n| demographics1_info1             = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code                     = 521105\n| area_code_type                  = Telephone code\n| area_code                       = +91-8656\n| registration_plate              = AP 16\n| footnotes                       = \n| government_footnotes            = <ref name=civicbody>{{cite web|title=Municipalities, Municipal Corporations & UDAs|url=http://dtcp.ap.gov.in:9090/webdtcp/Municipalities%20List-110.pdf|website=Directorate of Town and Country Planning|publisher=Government of Andhra Pradesh|accessdate=29 January 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128175528/http://dtcp.ap.gov.in:9090/webdtcp/Municipalities%20List-110.pdf|archivedate=28 January 2016|format=PDF}}</ref>\n| founder                         = \n| other_name                      = Bapulapadu\n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Andhra Pradesh, India\n| nickname                        = \n| settlement_type                 = [[Town]]\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = Hanuman Junction location in India\n| image_caption                   = \n| pushpin_map                     = India#India Andhra Pradesh\n| pushpin_relief                  = yes\n| pushpin_label_position          = \n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|16.63|N|80.97|E|display=inline,title}}\n| established_date                = \n| subdivision_type                = [[Country]]\n| subdivision_name                = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Andhra Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts in Andhra Pradesh|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Krishna District|Krishna]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[List of mandals in Andhra Pradesh|District]]\n| subdivision_name3               = [[Bapulapadu mandal|Bapulapadu]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| official_name                   = \n}}\n[[File:Hanuman Junction Board.jpg|thumb|Board on NH-5 in H.Junction]]\n'''Hanuman Junction ''' is a town which lies between the borders of [[Krishna district|Krishna]] and [[West Godavari district]]s of [[Andhra Pradesh]] state in [[India]]. Hanuman Junction gets its name because it lies in the [[Junction (road)|X-Junction]] of [[National Highway 16 (India)|NH-16]] & AH-45.\n== Religious worships ==\n[[File:Hanuman temple overview.jpg|alt=an image of temple from road|thumb|206x206px|Sri Abhayanjaneya Swami Vari Devasthanam temple.]]\n'''<u>Sri Abhaya Anjaneya Swamy Temple :</u>'''\n<br />\n'''History of temple:'''\n\nHanuman Junction is on  National Highway No. 16, we are looking at the statue of Anjaneya Swamy. we bow to the statue. An icon of Hanuman Junction. There is so much to say about this statue. The idol is located on the border of Krishna district and West Godavari districts. Swami's feet bordered the districts of West Godavari and Krishna.the Sanctuary is in  the  West Godavari district , the stairs are in the Krishna district. The face of the statue of Anjaneya Swamy has more human features than monkey. Another specialty is the junction of four main roads. Eluru Road, Gudivada Road, Nuzvid Road, Vijayawada Road and the four roads intersect here. The statue of Swami was installed in the year 1938.\n[[File:Hanuman Swami statue.jpg|alt=swami idol|thumb|212x212px|The Beautiful Idol is decorated everyday and worshiped whole Day until night.when it comes to Tuesday it becomes a very special place to vehicle owners to take blessings of lord anjanaya swami. ]]\n\n<br />\n'''Who made this statue? How did Hanuman Junction get its name?'''\n\nPreviously, this place was ruled by Shri MR Apparao, a nomadic jamindar.\n\nHis father, Sri Meka Venkatadri Bahadur, established the statue of Lord Anjaneya in 1938.\n\nZamindar Meka Venkatadri came to the junction of Bahadur Hanuman junction with a tremendous appetite for food. It is full of shrubs, bends, thorns and bushes. Zamindar's hunger has increased. Meanwhile a miracle happened. Suddenly a monkey came and put a banana in Zamindar's hand and disappeared. When the hungry Zamindar eats the fruit, he has a lot of energy.\n\nSensing that the Anjaneya Swami  had come in the form of a monkey and handed him a banana, the statue of Sri Anjaneya Swamy, who was in a state of devotion, was supposed to be installed there.\n\nThe statue was erected by Lord Anjaneya Swamy to protect the devotees from the clutches of evil spirits and set up the Hanuman Junction, a four-lane junction. While in Ramayan when Sri Rama Swami is in the Dandakaranyam, Anjaneyaswamy came and offered the banana fruit to Swami. they built a statue of Anjaneya Swami representing \"offering bannas to rama\" in this junction and the roadside road opposite the Anjaneyaswamy temple.\n\nSri Abhaya Anjaneya swamy temple can be categorised under Religious places and is a popular tourist place in Hanuman Junction. This Sri Abhaya Anjaneya swamy temple draws huge crowds from the neighbouring places of Hyderabad, Vizag, Vijayawada, Tirupathi, Srisailam, Karimnagar, Nellore, Warangal, Basara, Kadapa.\n[[File:Sitha Rama Dasanjaneya swami.png|alt=sitha rama dasanjaneya swami |thumb|The idol is the largest statue around the area , its 45 Feet tall statue  looking stunning looks and beautiful from far. |298x298px]]\n\n\n\n\n<br />\n==== <u>Sitha Rama Dasanjaneya Swami Temple:</u> ====\nLate Sri Palnati Satyanarayana Garu established the Sita Rama Dasanjaneya swami temple in Epuru, Hanuman Junction. Adjacent to that temple Hanuman statue of 45 feet is erected  in the year 2015. It is the tallest statue of Hanuman in Hanuman Junction. It is located in the village of Epuru, approximately 1.5&nbsp;km from Hanuman Junction. Epuru Dasanjaneeya Swamy Temple is a statue in depicting Abhaya Anjaneeya Swamy. This statue was inaguratuated on 23 February 2015 which stands 45 feet tall.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}\n== Transport ==\nHanuman Junction lies on [[Eluru]] \u2013 [[Vijayawada]] section of [[Asian Highway 45|AH-45]]. APS RTC runs bus services from Eluru, Vijayawada and Rajahmundry. Nuzividu Railway Station serves Junction.\n\nRegular bus facility from Eluru,Vijayawada,Gudivada and Nuzvid .And Nuzvid railway station is just 2 Km away from town.\n\nfrequently running autos and buses are available.\n\n<br /> Bus Route form Vijayawada is 252 S, 252 B ,252\n\n== Education ==\nThe primary and secondary school education is imparted by government, aided and private schools, under the ''School Education Department'' of the state.<ref>{{cite web|title=School Education Department|url=http://rmsaap.nic.in/Notification_TSG_2015.pdf|publisher=School Education Department, Government of Andhra Pradesh|accessdate=7 November 2016|format=PDF|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151227185018/http://rmsaap.nic.in/Notification_TSG_2015.pdf|archivedate=27 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Department of School Education \u2013 Official AP State Government Portal {{!}} AP State Portal|url=http://www.ap.gov.in/department/organizations/school-education/|website=www.ap.gov.in|accessdate=7 November 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107155331/http://www.ap.gov.in/department/organizations/school-education/|archivedate=7 November 2016}}</ref> The medium of instruction followed by different schools are English, Telugu.\n\nEven Higher Education  Like Intermediate colleges,Degree college, and Hotel Management colleges are available in and near Hanuman junction.\n\n== Hospitals and Medication ==\nSeetha Maha Lakshmi Nursing Home - maintained by DR.Dutta Rama Chandra Rao  Garu from many years giving best medicine and treatment .It has been recently developed and reconstruction work has been done during early months of 2019.\n\nand many mini hospitals  like aims and  RMP Doctors.\n\n'''\"But still have to go too long to major operations and emergency situations.\"'''\n\n== Food and Life Style ==\nThis Town is a business center for local villages and life style is being spread to locals through this town.\n\nhere we can have small restaurants and street foods, sweet shops, and the food style is being developing and new restaurants , food cultures have been introduced to town.\n\nAnd even in clothing and branding.     \n\nHave Movie-Theaters , shops , Grocery's , Beauty parlors and more is coming-up .     \n\nThe Town  got a lot of growth rate from past 3 years by maintaining this speed this town would me most developed town around .      \n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of statues by height]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Hanuman Junction}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Krishna district]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2018}}\n{{For|the same-titled 2001 Telugu film by [[M. Raja]]|Hanuman Junction (film)}}{{Infobox settlement\n| n